Re: On IRC bootstrapping

Bitcointalk

2010-06-18 17:28:18 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The SVN version now uses IRC first and if that fails it falls back to a
   hardcoded list of seed nodes.  There are enough seed nodes now that
   many of them should still be up by the time of the next release.  It
   only briefly connects to a seed node to get the address list and then
   disconnects, so your connections drop back to zero for while.  At that
   point, be patient.  Itʼs only slow to get connected the first time.
   This means TOR users wonʼt need to -addnode anymore, itʼll get
   connected automatically.
